README
======

Introduction
------------

The pytrash is a command line interface for the the gnome trash can.
The pytrash includes the follow script:

- trash
    removes files or directories to the GNOME Trash.

See '--help' option for usage. 

INSTALL
-------

Edit a PATH variable of a pytrash.py file to specify the correct path for the gnome trash can.
The deafult path is a '.local/share/Trash'.

$ python setup.py install

HOW TO USE
----------

Make a alias for the trash script as the "rm" command.

    $ alias rm=trash

